<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,775,1727,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">
DIAGNOSIS. — Sponge encrusting to slightly massive, with megascleres that are exclusively microspined oxeas; pseudobirotuled microscleres present in two distinct 
<typeStatus box="[351,404,1780,1804]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">types</typeStatus>
; gemmuloscleres present as sanidasters inserted radially in the gemmules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[131,776,1851,2026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">
ECOLOGY. — The specimens were collected in clear waters of artificial environment, in fish farm tanks walls measuring 
<quantity box="[664,725,1877,1905]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" unit="m" value="1.5">1.5 m</quantity>
³ and 
<quantity box="[133,198,1904,1932]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
³, that are supplied with water from São Francisco River, with depth ranging from 
<quantity box="[328,390,1931,1955]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
to 
<specimenCount box="[423,469,1931,1955]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="generic">
<quantity box="[423,465,1931,1955]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[131,776,1851,2026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">ETYMOLOGY. — The specific epithet refers to of morphology of the sponges’ gemmuloscleres: sanidaster.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="454" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1457,1204,1518]" box="[813,1111,1204,1230]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">
DESCRIPTION OF 
<typeStatus box="[1000,1111,1209,1228]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1457,1204,1518]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">
UFPEPOR1105 is encrusting, forming a thin layer on the substrate. Colour is dark green 
<emphasis box="[1152,1223,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">in vivo</emphasis>
and beige in ethanol. Megascleres acanthoxea (234.2-269.1-310.7 / 9.7-12.7- 19.1 Μm), microscleres with 
<specimenCount box="[1131,1237,1332,1358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of pseudobirotules: 
<typeStatus box="[814,860,1364,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">type</typeStatus>
1 (short shaft), (11.9-18.4-26.3 / 2.4 // 3.6-4.9-7.2 Μm) more abundant than 
<typeStatus box="[1044,1090,1396,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">type</typeStatus>
2 (long shaft), (31.1-48.6-71.7 / 2.4-3.9-4.8 Μm), sanidaster gemmuloscleres (71.7-82.8-95.6 / 4.8-7.3-19.1 // 3.2-6.3-9.7 Μm), gemmules (406.3-466.4- 501.9 Μm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1457,1555,2028]" box="[813,957,1555,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1457,1555,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[130,776,1746,2028]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="454" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Silva &amp; Calheira, 2015" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Silva &amp; Calheira" authorityYear="2015" box="[813,1177,1586,1612]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spongillidae" genus="Corvoheteromeyenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spongillida" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="sanidastosclera" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[813,1177,1586,1612]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1186,1247,1587,1613]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by presence of sanidaster gemmuloscleres (acanthostrongyles with tuberculate spines, 
<figureCitation box="[1016,1097,1650,1677]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[134,143,1351,1369]" captionTargetBox="[134,1460,215,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[795,1459,669,1125]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 5. — Spicules of Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp. (UFPEPOR1105), spicular components: A, B, megasclere acanthoxea;C, D, microscleres pseu- dobirotules; E, gemmuloscleres sanidaster; F, gemmule; G, foramen of gemmule; H, gemmules with gemmuloscleres inserted radially. Scale bars: A, H, 100 μm; B-D, 10 μm; E, 30 μm; F, 300 μm; G, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). The shape of this sponge ranges from encrustant to slightly massive, not exceeding 
<quantity box="[1369,1425,1682,1709]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
of thickness. Colour dark green 
<emphasis box="[1118,1186,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">in vivo</emphasis>
and becoming light green (
<figureCitation box="[818,932,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1089,1107]" captionTargetBox="[131,1456,213,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-442@4.[131,794,213,675]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2.— Corvoheteromeyenia Ezcurra de Drago,1979,Paulo Afonso municipality,Bahia State,in the shores of São Francisco River,Brazil:A, B, Corvoheteromeyenia heterosclera (Ezcurra de Drago, 1974), in situ; C, Corvoheteromeyenia heterosclera, in situ, on the left side and Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp., in situ, on the right side; D, Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp., in situ. Scale bars: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156469/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">Fig. 2C, D</figureCitation>
) or beige in ethanol. Consistency soft, easily torn. Gemmules distributed throughout the sponge but concentrated near the substrate.Megascleres fusiform, slightly curved oxeas (225.4-307.7-373.5 / 6.4-12.8-19.3 Μm), smooth or with recurved sparse microspinations, ranging from simple to compound (
<figureCitation box="[976,1091,1905,1932]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[134,143,1351,1369]" captionTargetBox="[134,1460,215,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[795,1459,669,1125]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 5. — Spicules of Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp. (UFPEPOR1105), spicular components: A, B, megasclere acanthoxea;C, D, microscleres pseu- dobirotules; E, gemmuloscleres sanidaster; F, gemmule; G, foramen of gemmule; H, gemmules with gemmuloscleres inserted radially. Scale bars: A, H, 100 μm; B-D, 10 μm; E, 30 μm; F, 300 μm; G, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">Fig. 5A, B</figureCitation>
). Pseudobirotuled microscleres of 
<specimenCount box="[813,914,1938,1964]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[927,1044,1937,1964]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[134,143,1351,1369]" captionTargetBox="[134,1460,215,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[795,1459,669,1125]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 5. — Spicules of Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp. (UFPEPOR1105), spicular components: A, B, megasclere acanthoxea;C, D, microscleres pseu- dobirotules; E, gemmuloscleres sanidaster; F, gemmule; G, foramen of gemmule; H, gemmules with gemmuloscleres inserted radially. Scale bars: A, H, 100 μm; B-D, 10 μm; E, 30 μm; F, 300 μm; G, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">Fig. 5C, D</figureCitation>
): 
<typeStatus box="[1063,1109,1938,1964]" pageId="4" pageNumber="453">type</typeStatus>
1, (11.9-18.9-35.4 / 2.4-3.0-3.2 // 3.6-6.2-9.7 Μm) most common, with three or four large hooks forming rotules and a short shaft that can be smooth or spined (
<figureCitation box="[249,335,1746,1773]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[134,143,1351,1369]" captionTargetBox="[134,1460,215,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[795,1459,669,1125]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 5. — Spicules of Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp. (UFPEPOR1105), spicular components: A, B, megasclere acanthoxea;C, D, microscleres pseu- dobirotules; E, gemmuloscleres sanidaster; F, gemmule; G, foramen of gemmule; H, gemmules with gemmuloscleres inserted radially. Scale bars: A, H, 100 μm; B-D, 10 μm; E, 30 μm; F, 300 μm; G, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156478/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); and 
<typeStatus box="[405,451,1746,1772]" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">type</typeStatus>
2, (31.1-56.6-90.2 / 2.4-5.9- 9.7 Μm), less common with more discreet hooks forming rotules and a longer shaft than 
<typeStatus box="[424,470,1810,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">type</typeStatus>
1, with simple to compound microspines distributed equitably along the shaft (
<figureCitation box="[671,758,1841,1868]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[134,143,1351,1369]" captionTargetBox="[134,1460,215,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[795,1459,669,1125]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 5. — Spicules of Corvoheteromeyenia sanidastosclera n. sp. (UFPEPOR1105), spicular components: A, B, megasclere acanthoxea;C, D, microscleres pseu- dobirotules; E, gemmuloscleres sanidaster; F, gemmule; G, foramen of gemmule; H, gemmules with gemmuloscleres inserted radially. Scale bars: A, H, 100 μm; B-D, 10 μm; E, 30 μm; F, 300 μm; G, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156478/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5156472" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5156472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5156472/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="454" startId="5.[132,143,1076,1094]" targetBox="[134,1460,216,1029]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[132,1457,1075,1139]" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">
FIG. 3. — Spicules of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ezcurra de Drago, 1974) (UFPEPOR 1771)" authorityName="UFPEPOR" authorityYear="1771" baseAuthorityName="Ezcurra de Drago" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[306,938,1075,1094]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spongillidae" genus="Corvoheteromeyenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spongillida" pageId="5" pageNumber="454" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="heterosclera">
<emphasis box="[306,584,1075,1094]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">Corvoheteromeyenia heterosclera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="EZCURRA DE DRAGO I." box="[593,789,1076,1094]" pageId="5" pageNumber="454" pagination="233 - 240" refId="ref5459" refString="EZCURRA DE DRAGO I. 1974. - Las especies sudamericanas de Corvomeyenia Weltner (Porifera, Spongillidae). Physis 33 (87): 233 - 240." type="journal article" year="1974">Ezcurra de Drago, 1974</bibRefCitation>
) (UFPEPOR1771)
</taxonomicName>
,spicular components: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1129,1142,1076,1094]" pageId="5" pageNumber="454">A</emphasis>
, 
